					<p class="introducaoPost">
						PMBOK, for those who don’t know it, it’s a best practices guide 
						for project management published by PMI (Project Management Institute), 
						one of the main references on the subject. According to the PMBOK, 
						the definition of a project is "a temporary effort undertaken to 
						create a product, service or exclusive result." i.e., a project 
						is not something continuous, endless or repetitive and cyclical.
					</p>
				</div>
				
